cdata.name: Bitcore
cdata.desc: Bitcore is a Bitcoin-based cryptocurrency created through a snapshot and airdrop process.Bitcore has 10 MB blocks with Segwit enabled which allows for the network to handle about 17.6 billion transactions per year. It also features an ASIC resistant pow algorithm, Timetravel10, and a difficult adjustment called 64_15 that ensures that there is no more than a 15 percent change in difficulty within a 64 block period.
